abstract: With many of the Egyptian activists at the vanguard of last year's revolution demoralized by the choice between two conservatives, journalists and bloggers reported a distinct lack of enthusiasm, and a low turnout of younger voters, in Saturday's presidential election runoff.

headline.main: Amid Tight Security and Low Expectations, Egypt Votes Again
